foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: * In the FY 2012 FOIA Annual Report, ITA reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY2011 as "32." One request from 2011 was re-opened, changing the number to "33." Therefore, the number of requests pending as of the start of FY 2011 has been amended to "33" in the FY 2012 report.

** In the FY 2011 FOIA Annual Report, NOAA reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY 2011 as "179." This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of 63 requests is due to requests fulfilled in FY 2011, but not documented until FY 2012. The correct number is "116." Therefore, the number of requests pending as of the start of FY 2011 has been amended to "116" in the FY 2012 report.

***In the FY 2011 FOIA Annual Report, the number of requests pending at the end of FY 2011 was reported as "296." Due to the amendment in the number of requests pending as of the start of FY 2012 for ITA and NOAA (see footnotes above), the number of requests pending as of the start of FY 2011 for the agency overall has been amended to "234."

foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: * Assistant General Counsel for Administration (AGC/Admin.) processes the appeals for all the Department of Commerce components, except for PTO.

** In the FY2011 Annual FOIA Report, AGC/Admin. reported the number of appeals pending as of the end of FY2011 as "47." This number was reported incorrectly. The correct number pending as of the end of FY 2011 should have been "56." Therefore, the number of appeals pending as of the start of FY2012 for AGC/Admin. has been amended to "56"in the FY2012 Annual FOIA Report.

foia:BackloggedRequestComparisonSection.foia:FootnoteText: * In FY 2011 NOAA reported "135" requests backlogged in error. The error in reporting occurred when requests closed in FY 2011, but not documented in the FY 2011 Annual FOIA Report. The correct number is 74.

** In the FY 2011 Annual FOIA Report, NOAA reported the number of requests pending at the end of FY 2011 as "179." This number was reported incorrectly. The difference of 63 requests is due to requests fulfilled in FY 2011, but not documented until FY 2012. The correct number is "116." Therefore, the number of requests pending as of the start of FY 2011 has been amended to "116" in the FY 2012 Annual FOIA Report.
